response: "{ \"title\": \"Sum of Proper Divisors (Medium)\", \"description\": \"The sum of the proper divisors of a number N is given by \u03a3(k) for 1 \u2264 k < N. Write a function `sum_of_divisors` that calculates the sum of the proper divisors of a given integer.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer for which to calculate the sum of its proper divisors.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of the proper divisors of the input integer.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\nimport math\\n\\ndef sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            total += i\\n    return total + 1\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_divisors(220) == 284\", \"assert sum_of_divisors(12345) == 12430\", \"assert sum_of_divisors(10) == 18\"] }"
